/*
:name: signed_one_bit_cmp
:type: equiv
:verilog_top: signed_one_bit_cmp.p
:pyrope_top: signed_one_bit_cmp.p
*/

// KNOWN-FAILING (fixme tracker). Ordered comparison of a 1-bit SIGNED value is
// computed UNSIGNED, so this REFUTES today.
//
//   signed(x#[3]) reinterprets the u1 bit as s1 = {-1, 0}; a set bit is -1, so
//   `signed(x#[3]) < 0` MUST equal x[3]. It does not.
//
// ROOT CAUSE (debugged): LiveHD stores a value's width as `bits = magnitude+1`
// and re-derives signedness from it (tolg `bind_result` drops the per-op signed
// hint). A 1-bit value has 0 magnitude bits, so its sign is dropped — it reads
// UNSIGNED everywhere. pass/lec/encode.cpp LT then uses BITVECTOR_ULT (signed
// only when BOTH operands are signed), and cgen emits an unsigned `reg`.
//   * EQUALITY (== -1), WIDENING (s8 + s1), and ROUND-TRIP (unsigned(signed(b)))
//     are all CORRECT — only ordered compares (< <= > >=) of a 1-bit signed are
//     wrong, and only at W==1 (W>=2 is correct).
//   * Fixing it means letting a 1-bit value carry a sign (touches the core
//     bits/sign convention + pass/lec/encode.cpp + cgen) — deferred.
//   * Related declared-`:s1` range bug ([1,1] -> [-1,0]) was FIXED in prp2lnast.
comb p(x:u8) -> (b:bool) {
  b = signed(x#[3]) < 0
}
